%A0%26quot%3Byes%26quot%3B%20through%20a%20crippling%20series%20of%20questions%20about%20bank%20docs%20he%20personally%20signed.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatty-trump-has-hard-time-yes-no-questions-witness-stand-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDonald%20Trump%20let%20fly%20a%20fusillade%20of%20insults%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20witness%20stand%20at%20his%20Manhattan%20fraud%20trial%20Monday%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-fixates-mar-a-lago-value-fraud-trial-testimony-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecalling%20the%20judge%20a%20%26quot%3Bfraud%2C%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fa%3Edismissing%20the%20New%20York%20attorney%20general%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20political%20hack%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20huffing%20that%20the%20state%20lawyer%20questioning%20him%20%26quot%3Bshould%20be%20ashamed%26quot%3B%20of%20himself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20boasts%2C%20too%2C%20of%20his%20%26quot%3Bbeautiful%26quot%3B%20Scottish%20golf%20course%2C%20of%20his%20great%20wealth%20%E2%80%93%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20cash%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20testified%20%E2%80%93%20and%20of%20Mar-a-Lago's%20%26quot%3Bvery%20big%20ballroom.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20behind%20his%20many%20tantrums%20and%20tangents%20(mentions%20of%20George%20Washington%20and%20windmills%20among%20them)%2C%20Trump%20suffered%2C%20legally%20speaking%2C%20on%20that%20witness%20stand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20afternoon%2C%20the%20former%20president%20was%20led%20for%20half%20an%20hour%20through%20a%20crippling%20series%20of%20questions%20about%20banking%20documents%20that%2C%20between%202012%20and%202016%2C%20he%20personally%20signed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20%E2%80%93%20sounding%20sometimes%20defiant%2C%20sometimes%20indifferent%20%E2%80%93%20the%20former%20president%20and%20current%20GOP%20frontrunner%20shrugged%20%26quot%3Byes%2C%26quot%3B%20again%20and%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20as%20if%20Trump%20were%20unaware%20of%20the%20accumulating%20injuries%20he%20suffered%20under%20the%20figurative%20knife-work%20of%20his%20questioner%2C%20Kevin%20C.%20Wallace%2C%20a%20seasoned%20state%20attorney%20who%20has%20pursued%20him%20for%20three%20years%20as%20senior%20counsel%20to%20state%20Attorney%20General%20Letitia%20James.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20end%20of%20his%20daylong%20testimony%2C%20Trump%20had%20squinted%20at%2C%20and%20paged%20through%2C%20a%20six-inch-thick%20set%20of%20documents%20concerning%20more%20than%20%24400%20million%20in%20bank%20loans%20and%20%24139%20million%20in%20property%20sale%20profits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bank%20loan%20documents%20all%20bore%20his%20signature%2C%20Trump%20confirmed%2C%20not%20that%20this%20could%20be%20disputed%2C%20given%20the%20characteristic%20Sharpie%20zigzags%20on%20the%20signatory%20pages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Trump%20then%20answered%20%26quot%3Byes%2C%26quot%3B%20over%20and%20over%2C%20as%20Wallace%2C%20always%20keeping%20his%20voice%20matter-of-fact%2C%20walked%20Trump%20through%20his%20more%20significant%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWallace%20made%20the%20same%20series%20of%20queries%20for%20each%20of%20Trump's%20three%20Deutsche%20Bank%20loans%2C%20one%20for%20his%20Miami%20golf%20course%2C%20one%20for%20his%20Chicago%20skyscraper%2C%20and%20one%20for%20the%20renovation%20of%20the%20Old%20Post%20Office%2C%20in%20Washington%2C%20D.C.%2C%20into%20a%20luxury%20hotel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20was%20asked%20for%20each%20property%20whether%2C%20in%20the%20underlying%20loan%20documents%2C%20he%20had%20promised%20the%20bank%20that%20his%20annual%20net%20worth%20statements%20are%20%26quot%3Btrue%20and%20correct%20in%20all%20material%20respects.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIs%20it%20true%2C%20Trump%20was%20asked%20by%20Wallace%2C%20that%20to%20get%20and%20keep%20these%20loans%2C%20you%20promised%20to%20maintain%20%2450%20million%20in%20cash%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20is%20it%20true%2C%20he%20was%20asked%2C%20that%20you%20likewise%20promised%20to%20maintain%20a%20net%20worth%2C%20as%20the%20Deutsche%20Bank%20documents%20spelled%20it%20out%2C%20of%20%26quot%3Bnot%20less%20than%20Two%20Billion%20Five%20Hundred%20Million%20(%242%2C500%2C000%2C000)%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20Trump%20answered%20again%20and%20again.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSounds%20great%20to%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20at%20another%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20Trump%20being%20Trump%2C%20there%20were%20tangents%20and%20tantrums%20mixed%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20loan%20was%20paid%20off%20in%20full%20with%20no%20default%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20protested%2C%20when%20asked%20to%20look%20at%20%26quot%3BPlaintiff's%20exhibit%20Number%20312%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20lengthy%202012%20loan%20agreement%20for%20the%20Chicago%20highrise%2C%20Trump%20International%20Hotel%20%26amp%3B%20Tower.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20the%20bank%20was%20thrilled%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20continued.%20%26quot%3BIf%20the%20interest%20was%20due%20on%20a%20Saturday%2C%20I%20paid%20the%20interest%20on%20a%20Friday.%20The%20bank%20liked%20me%20very%20much%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAgain%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Wallace%2C%20when%20asked%20about%20the%20Old%20Post%20Office%20loan%2C%20%26quot%3Bmy%20net%20worth%20was%20far%20greater%20than%20what's%20on%20the%20financial%20statements.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20know%20what%20you're%20getting%20at%2C%20but%20keep%20going%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20added%2C%20making%20a%20brushing-off%20motion%20with%20his%20hand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWallace%20did%20keep%20going.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20space%20of%20a%20half%20hour%2C%20Trump%20admitted%20that%20for%20all%20three%20key%20loans%2C%20he%20believed%20the%20bank%20relied%20on%20his%20promise%20that%20his%20annual%20net-worth%20statements%20were%20%26quot%3Btrue%20and%20correct%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20his%20cash%20and%20total%20assets%20hit%20the%20bank's%20targets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%