v's%20death%20caused%20%26quot%3Bunspeakable%20pain%26quot%3B%20and%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bheavy%20loss%26quot%3B%20not%20only%20for%20himself%20but%20for%20the%20military%20as%20well.%20He%20said%20Chastiakov%20had%20been%20a%20%26quot%3Breliable%20shoulder%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20top%20general%20since%20the%20beginning%20of%20Russia's%20full-scale%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20in%20February%202022%20and%20that%20his%20death%20will%20be%20investigated.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChastiakov's%20wife%20said%20the%20item%20that%20exploded%20was%20a%20grenade%20inside%20a%20gift%20bag%2C%20Ukrainska%20Pravda%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pravda.com.ua%2Feng%2Fnews%2F2023%2F11%2F6%2F7427515%2F%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20citing%20an%20unnamed%20law%20enforcement%20source.%20The%20gift%20bag%20also%20contained%20a%20bottle%20of%20alcohol%20and%20shot%20glasses%20that%20looked%20like%20grenades%2C%20per%20the%20report.%20Chastiakov's%2013-year-old%20son%20was%20reportedly%20also%20taken%20to%20the%20hospital%20with%20serious%20injuries.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInitial%20reports%20on%20the%20circumstances%20of%20Chastiakov's%20death%20left%20much%20unclear%2C%20but%20Ihor%20Klymenko%2C%20Ukraine's%20minister%20of%20internal%20affairs%2C%20later%20clarified%20that%20Chastiakov%20had%20returned%20home%20from%20work%20with%20gifts%20from%20his%20colleagues%2C%20one%20of%20them%20being%20a%20box%20of%20new%20Western-made%20grenades%2C%20which%20he%20then%20showed%20to%20his%20son.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKlymenko%20said%20in%20a%20Telegram%20message%20that%20an%20exchange%20between%20Chastiakov%20and%20his%20son%20led%20to%20the%20accidental%20detonation%20of%20one%20of%20the%20grenades.%20Police%20later%20found%20five%20more%20unexploded%20grenades%20at%20his%20residence%20and%20identified%20a%20Ukrainian%20soldier%20who%20gave%20them%20to%20Chastiakov.%20The%20soldier's%20office%20has%20been%20searched%2C%20and%20more%20grenades%20were%20found%20there%2C%20Klymenko%20said.%