ea-doesnt-mean-what-you-think-it-means%2F%5C%22%3Egained%20traction%20among%20Palestinians%20in%20the%201960s%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20they%20advocated%20for%20a%20single%20secular%2C%20democratic%20state%20extending%20across%20the%20entirety%20of%20the%20land%20historically%20known%20as%20%26quot%3BPalestine%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20includes%20both%20Israel%20and%20the%20Palestinian%20territories.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20the%20line%20taken%20by%20the%20Palestine%20Liberation%20Organization%20upon%20its%20founding%20by%20Yasser%20Arafat%20in%201964.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20the%20slogan%20did%20originate%20as%20a%20call%20for%20the%20dismantling%20of%20Israel%20as%20a%20Jewish%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Nassar%20notes%2C%20plenty%20of%20Palestinians%20did%20believe%20at%20the%20time%20that%20a%20realization%20of%20that%20vision%20would%20likely%20entail%20thousands%20of%20Jewish%20people%20voluntarily%20leaving%2C%20given%20that%20they%20would%20no%20longer%20live%20in%20an%20explicitly%20Jewish%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPalestinians%20viewed%20Israelis%20within%20the%20context%20of%20settler%20colonialism%2C%20believing%20Israel%20to%20be%20yet%20another%20European%20colony%20akin%20to%20Algeria.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIs%20it%20used%20by%20Hamas%3F%20Yes%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20leading%20Palestinian%20groups%20like%20the%20Palestine%20Liberation%20Organization%20(PLO)%20abandoned%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20one-state%20solution%20in%20favor%20of%20a%20two-state%20solution%20in%20the%201980s%20and%201990s%2C%20that%20mantle%20was%20opportunistically%20taken%20up%20by%20Hamas%2C%20an%20Islamist%20militant%20organization%20founded%20in%20the%20late%201980s%20that%20garnered%20support%20based%20on%20the%20perception%20that%20secular%20leaders%20in%20the%20PLO%20had%20given%20up%20too%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHamas%2C%20both%20a%20terrorist%20organization%20and%20a%20political%20party%20that%20has%20governed%20Gaza%20since%202007%2C%20uses%20the%20phrase%20in%20its%202017%20charter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHamas%20rejects%20any%20alternative%20to%20the%20full%20and%20complete%20liberation%20of%20Palestine%2C%20from%20the%20river%20to%20the%20sea%2C%26quot%3B%20reads%20article%2020%20of%20the%20charter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20even%20as%20it%20employed%20this%20phrase%2C%20the%20group%20signaled%20that%20it%20would%20accept%20a%20Palestinian%20state%20that%20did%20not%20include%20Israeli%20territory%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%26quot%3BWithout%20compromising%20its%20rejection%20of%20the%20Zionist%20entity%20and%20without%20relinquishing%20any%20Palestinian%20rights%2C%20Hamas%20considers%20the%20establishment%20of%20a%20fully%20sovereign%20and%20independent%20Palestinian%20state%2C%20with%20Jerusalem%20as%20its%20capital%20along%20the%20lines%20of%20the%204th%20of%20June%201967%2C%20with%20the%20return%20of%20the%20refugees%20and%20the%20displaced%20to%20their%20homes%20from%20which%20they%20were%20expelled%2C%20to%20be%20a%20formula%20of%20national%20consensus.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20broader%20contemporary%20meaning%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20slogan's%20origins%2C%20its%20meaning%20for%20Palestinians%20has%20grown%20broader%20over%20time%2C%20and%20is%20less%20about%20the%20eradication%20of%20Israel%20than%20the%20rights%20of%20Palestinians.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Palestinian-American%20scholar%20and%20activist%20Yousef%20Munayyer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjewishcurrents.org%2Fwhat-does-from-the-river-to-the-sea-really-mean%5C%22%3Ewrote%20in%20Jewish%20Currents%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202021%2C%20the%20phrase%20%E2%80%94%20particularly%20when%20it's%20invoked%20by%20activists%20%E2%80%94%20references%20the%20shared%20political%20struggles%20that%20Palestinians%20face%20today%20across%20Israel%20and%20the%20Palestinian%20territories%2C%20including%20discrimination%20in%20Israeli%20proper%2C%20military%20occupation%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%2C%20or%20conditions%20in%20Gaza%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsanders-gaza-is-open-air-prison-israel-violating-international-law-2023-10%5C%22%3Ehave%20been%20likened%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20an%20%26quot%3Bopen-air%20prison%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20phrase%20%26quot%3Bfrom%20the%20river%20to%20the%20sea%26quot%3B%20captures%20this%20future%20as%20no%20other%20can%2C%20because%20it%20encompasses%20the%20entire%20space%20in%20which%20Palestinian%20rights%20are%20denied%2C%26quot%3B%20Munayyer%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20in%20this%20space%20that%20Palestinians%20seek%20to%20live%20freely.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMunayyer%20argues%20that%20when%20Palestinians%20use%20the%20phrase%2C%20they%20are%20pushing%20for%20a%20%26quot%3Bstate%20in%20which%20Palestinians%20can%20live%20in%20their%20homeland%20as%20free%20and%20equal%20citizens%2C%20neither%20dominated%20by%20others%20nor%20dominating%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20slogan%20has%20also%20gained%20steam%20as%20the%20prospect%20of%20a%20two-state%20solution%20have%20grown%20ever%20slimmer%2C%20particularly%20as%20Israel%20continues%20to%20construct%20settlements%20deep%20within%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%20as%20international%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amnesty.org%2Fen%2Flatest%2Fnews%2F2022%2F02%2Fisraels-apartheid-against-palestinians-a-cruel-system-of-domination-and-a-crime-against-humanity%2F%5C%22%3Ehuman%20rights%20organizations%3C%2Fa%3E%20increasingly%20describe%20Israel%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hrw.org%2Freport%2F2021%2F04%2F27%2Fthreshold-crossed%2Fisraeli-authorities-and-crimes-apartheid-and-persecution%5C%22%3Ean%20apartheid%20state.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20worth%20noting%20that%20Palestinians%20aren't%20the%20only%20ones%20that%20have%20used%20a%20version%20of%20the%20phrase%20%E2%80%94%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu's%20political%20party%2C%20Likud%2C%20used%20the%20phrase%20in%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.je