1614%2Fimage-1478-193x300.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22193%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F06151614%2Fimage-1478-193x300.png%20193w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F06151614%2Fimage-1478.png%20462w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-683717%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Absent%20Color%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20a%2Fnil%20(Navayana%2C%20October%2025%2C%202023)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20unconscious%20is%20a%20world%20of%20repressed%20emotions%20and%20interests.%20It%20is%20where%20culture%20is%20hidden%2C%20where%20everything%20is%20in%20flux.%20It%20is%20structured%20like%20language.%20The%20word%20is%20unconscious%2C%20says%20Lacan.%20Words%20do%20not%20make%20meaning%20explicit.%20Rather%2C%20they%20open%20up%20endless%20possibilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPoetry%2C%20the%20art%20of%20words%2C%20comes%20forth%20from%20the%20unconscious.%20Trying%20to%20unveil%20the%20word%20in%20a%20poem%20is%20akin%20to%20unveiling%20the%20unconscious%20that%20has%20gone%20into%20its%20making.%20For%20those%20who%20share%20and%20know%20the%20life-world%20of%20a%20poet%2C%20entering%20this%20world%20is%20quite%20easy.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThose%20who%20have%20read%20Ezra%20Pound%2C%20Paul%20Celan%2C%20Jacques%20Lacan%2C%20Gilles%20Deleuze%2C%20and%20Slavoj%20%C5%BDi%C5%BEek%2C%20and%20who%20have%20also%20journeyed%20through%20the%20pains%20and%20sufferings%20of%20Dalit%20life%20in%20Kerala%2C%20may%20find%20Anil%E2%80%99s%20(a%2Fnil%E2%80%99s)%20poems%20easily%20accessible.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThough%20Anil%20and%20I%20have%20been%20friends%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%20his%20poetry%20still%20remains%20strange%20and%20enigmatic%20to%20me.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnavayana.org%2Fproducts%2Fthe-absent-color%2F%3Fv%3Dc86ee0d9d7ed%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Absent%20Color%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20trial%20for%20my%20imagination%3A%20I%20am%20a%20stranger%20traveling%20through%20a%2Fnil%E2%80%99s%20poetic%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20a%20difficult%20journey%20through%20a%20labyrinth%20of%20ideas.%20The%20following%20reading%20explores%20the%20wonders%20and%20dilemmas%20of%20this%20mysterious%20and%20difficult%20journey%2C%20with%20the%20firm%20conviction%20that%20such%20a%20journey%20into%20the%20unknown%20is%20a%20necessary%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20The%20self%20and%20the%20universe%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20poet%E2%80%99s%20name%20is%20a%20novel%20form%20of%20the%20word%20Anilan%2C%20which%20is%20the%20Malayalam%20equivalent%20of%20the%20Sanskrit%20%E2%80%9CAnil%E2%80%9D%2C%20meaning%20%3Cem%3Evayu%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20air%2C%20that%20which%20sustains%20life%20on%20earth.%20His%20official%20name%20%E2%80%93%20Anilkumar%20%E2%80%93%20reminds%20one%20of%20the%20Vayukumars%2C%20the%20valiant%20and%20heroic%20sons%20of%20the%20God%20Vayu.%20When%20the%20poet%20writes%20his%20name%20in%20English%20as%20%E2%80%9Ca%2Fnil%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20abandons%20all%20valour%2C%20heroism%2C%20and%20hierarchical%20symbols%20of%20power%20embodied%20in%20language%20and%20appears%20before%20us%20as%20a%2Fnil%2C%20a%2Fvoid%2C%20in%20the%20lowercase%2C%20bare%2C%20unassertive%2C%20claiming%20nothing.%20What%20does%20the%20poet%2C%20who%20claims%20only%20nothing%2C%20write%20in%20his%20poetry%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%3A%20What%20was%20formerly%20a%20world%20bound%20by%20Euclidean%20principles%2C%20where%20parallel%20lines%20refused%20to%20intersect%20and%20plane%20geometry%20reigned%20supreme%2C%20has%20changed%20into%20a%20Riemannian%20world%20of%20curved%20surfaces%2C%20where%20everything%20converges.%20This%20transition%20from%20Newtonian%20determinism%20to%20Einstein%E2%80%99s%20relativism%20that%20we%20saw%20in%20physics%20now%20affects%20the%20social%20sphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20poet%20expresses%20a%20desire%20for%20the%20intangible%2C%20the%20untouchable%2C%20to%20coalesce%20before%20his%20eyes.%20Yet%2C%20there%20remains%20a%20sorrow%20in%20his%20field%20of%20vision.%20There%20are%20no%20more%20boundaries%20that%20separate%20us%20into%20kinds.%20A%20world%20of%20absolute%20justice%20has%20arrived.%20The%20contemporary%20Dalit%20experience%2C%20exemplified%20by%20the%20persistent%20denial%20of%20social%20justice%20and%20stratagems%20of%20anti-reservation%20politics%2C%20finds%20its%20anchor%20in%20these%20lines.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBorrowing%20its%20title%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.poetryfoundation.org%2Fpoems%2F54319%2Fcanto-xlv%5C%22%3EEzra%20Pound%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3ECanto%20XLV%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20poem%20%3Cem%3ENo%20Clear%20Demarcation%3C%2Fem%3E%20weaves%20a%20tapestry%20of%20thought%2C%20intertwining%20Pound%E2%80%99s%20denunciations%20of%20an%20unnatural%20economic%20order%20indifferent%20to%20production%20with%20contemporary%20Indian%20reality.%20In%20this%20juxtaposition%2C%20we%20briefly%20glimpse%20at%20the%20unification%20of%20the%20working%20class.%20Yet%20it%20mirrors%20the%20paradoxes%20of%20Pound%E2%80%99s%20intellectual%20trajectory%2C%20when%20he%20rejected%20capitalism%2C%20only%20to%20embrace%20fascism%20%E2%80%93%20a%20contradiction%20that%20seems%20to%20echo%20through%20the%20intricacies%20of%20Dalit%20existence%2C%20far%20removed%20from%20the%20abyss%20of%20%E2%80%98untouchability%E2%80%99%20yet%20fraught%20with%20desolation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20Einstein%20eloquently%20described%20a%20world%20where%20all%20physical%20aspects%20were%20relative%2C%20his%20definition%20of%20the%20speed%20of%20light%20as%20an%20absolute%2C%20unchanging%2C%20and%20non-relative%20value%20paradoxically%20aligns%20with%20established%20norms%20and%20conventions.%20Many%20apparent%20groundbreaking%20shifts%20and%20dramatic%20upheavals%20in%20theory%2C%20upon%20close%20examination%2C%20tend%20towards%20becoming%20nothing%20more%20than%20ordering%20principles%20in%20practical%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20a%2Fnil%E2%80%99s%20poetry%2C%20scientific%20concepts%20are%20transformed%20into%20metaphors.%20Terms%20like%20%E2%80%9Cmanifolds%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Credshift%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cadiabatic%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Crefraction%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20%E2%80%9Cholography%E2%80%9D%20stand%20out.%20In%20the%20poem%20titled%20%3Cem%3EDeclaration%20of%20Independence%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20we%20see%20the%20reality%20of%20a%20Dalit%E2%80%99s%20life%20scrutinised%20from%20the%20perspective%20of%20scientific%20theories.%20Is%20the%20universe%20still%20expanding%3F%20Are%20the%20galaxies%20moving%20away%3F%20Meanwhile%2C%20Dalit%20life%20contracts%20relentlessly%2C%20like%20a%20star%20collapsing%20into%20itself%2C%20into%20singularity%20%E2%80%93%20a%20profound%20analogy%20for%20the%20inexorable%20compression%20of%20their%20existence.%20Dalits%20declare%20their%20distinctiveness%2C%20an%20unwavering%20resolve%20to%20stand%20alone%2C%20resisting%20attempts%20to%20%E2%80%9Csterilise%E2%80%9D%20them%2C%20much%20like%20a%20star%20that%20undergoes%20profound%20metamorphosis%20and%20becomes%20a%20black%20hole%2C%20retaining%20its%20singularity%20amidst%20the%20cosmic%20expanse.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERooted%20in%20skulls%20and%20fed%20on%20blood%20%E2%80%A6%20chameleons%20are%20creatures%20that%20await%20their%20fate%20among%20debris%20and%20waste%20bottles.%20All%20that%20the%20poet%20says%20through%20the%20metaphors%20of%20skulls%20and%20chameleons%20is%20made%20denser%20with%20allusions%20to%20the%20films%20of%20Eisenstein%20and%20Tarkovsky.%20The%20mention%20of%20%3Cem%3EOctober%3C%2Fem%3E%20reminds%20us%20of%20the%20Russian%20Revolution.%20The%20image%20of%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20October%20sky%E2%80%9D%20of%20Soviet%20initiative%20looms%20over%20us%2C%20never%20to%20be%20recaptured%2C%20never%20to%20be%20repeated.%20It%20readily%20takes%20you%20to%20Al%20Stewart%E2%80%99s%20song%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3Dh0N1onEqWn0%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Roads%20to%20Moscow%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAnd%20the%20pale%20sun%20of%20October%20whispers%20the%20snow%20will%20soon%20be%20coming%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cem%3EAnd%20I%20wonder%20when%20I%E2%80%99ll%20be%20home%20again%20and%20the%20morning%20answers%20%E2%80%98Never%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cem%3EAnd%20the%20evening%20sighs%2C%20and%20the%20steely%20Russian%20skies%20go%20on%20forever.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EOne%20of%20the%20poems%20about%20poetry%20is%20titled%20%E2%80%9CImagining%20October%E2%80%9D.%20Poetry%20brings%20only%20blackness.%20Amma%E2%80%94Mother%2C%20the%20microcosm%20of%20the%20poet%E2%80%99s%20songs%2C%20what%20makes%20art%20possible%E2%80%94is%20crushed%20under%20the%20weight%20of%20multiple%20gravitational%20pulls.%20This%20reality%20is%20not%20one%20accepted%20readily.%20And%20yet%20it%20remains%20invisible%2C%20as%20if%20natural.%20It%20cannot%20call%20attention%20to%20itself%20because%20it%20is%20made%20to%20seem%20so%20mundane%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWords%2C%20boughs%2C%20spirit%2C%20spine%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cem%3ECrushed%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cem%3EBeneath%20the%20severe%20heaviness%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cem%3EOf%20multiple%20gravities.%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cem%3ENo%20%C3%A9clat%20for%20the%20real%20act.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EConsider%20the%20very%20title%20of%20a%2Fnil%E2%80%99s%20book.%20Sight%20and%20colours%20are%20always%20problematic%20for%20him.%20In%20the%20preface%20(called%20%E2%80%9CPre%20Face%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20is%20also%20written%20as%20a%20poem)%2C%20he%20writes%20that%20he%20was%20partially%20blind%20at%20an%20early%20age.%20But%20the%20impairment%20in%20the%20outer%20eye%20led%20to%20insight%2C%20and%20inner%20vision.%20Contemporary%20lenses%20are%20tinted.%20Lenses%20come%20contracted%20to%20colours.%20The%20contrast%20between%20the%20one%20who%20desires%20a%20true%20vision%20of%20colors%20and%20one%20who%20seeks%20to%20be%20engulfed%20in%20the%20colourlessness%20and%20colourfulness%20of%20the%20world%20as%20it%20appears%20forms%20the%20overall%20theme%20of%20these%20poems.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20my%20turn%2C%20I%20realize%2C%20to%20be%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cem%3EAuthentic%20to%20the%20unfolding%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cem%3EAnd%20I%20am%20polishing%20the%20lens%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cem%3EOf%20the%20scratched%20glasses%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cem%3ETo%20have%20clarity%20for%20Eye%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EClarity%20is%20never%20an%20accident.%20(Unplannable%20Supplement)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnd%20so%20the%20poet%20gains%20courage%20and%20awareness.%20These%20lines%20remind%20us%20of%20Spinoza%2C%20a%20philosopher%20who%20was%20also%20a%20lens-grinder%2C%20and%20whose%20epistemological%20project%20was%20concerned%20with%20the%20self%20and%20the%20universe.%20Borges%20described%20him%20thus%3A%20He%20works%20a%20hard%20crystal%3A%20the%20Infinite.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20uncertainties%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20a%2Fnil%2C%20an%20a%2Fvarna%20who%20in%20modern%20terms%20is%20a%20Dalit%2C%20the%20absence%20of%20colours%20(varna)%20in%20the%20poem%20has%20socio-political%20dimensions.%20At%20times%20it%20is%20recognised%20as%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EI%20still%20write%20poetry%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cem%3EAnd%20nothing%20happens%3B%20customary%20glance.%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cem%3EWhere%20is%20that%20leonine%20poise%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20move%2F%20Like%20habiru%2F%20Or%20do%20we%3F%E2%80%9D%20A%20perpetual%20spectre%20of%20self-doubt%20looms%20over%20the%20poet.%20The%20questions%20that%20lie%20in%20the%20laments%20of%20nomads%20and%20outcasts%20resound%20in%20this%20poem.%20Uncertainties%2C%20steadily%20accumulating%2C%20are%20palpable.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Unnameable%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20poet%E2%80%99s%20melancholy%20takes%20on%20a%20unique%20and%20distinctive%20quality.%20It%20transcends%20the%20typical%20discomfort%20with%20words%20that%20many%20poets%20experience.%20A%2Fnil%20sympathises%20with%20the%20Dalit-ness%20of%20the%20unnameable.%20The%20Habiru%E2%80%99s%20folkways%20are%20also%20attributed%20as%20unnameable.%20(The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.encyclopedia.com%2Freligion%2Fencyclopedias-almanacs-transcripts-and-maps%2Fhabiru-habiri%5C%22%3EHabiru%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20pre-dating%20the%20word%20Hebrew%2C%20finds%20reference%20in%20second-millennium%20BCE%20texts%20as%20people%20described%20as%20rebels%2C%20outlaws%2C%20raiders%2C%20mercenaries%2C%20bowmen%2C%20servants%2C%20slaves%2C%20and%20labourers.)%20To%20know%20each%20other%2C%20to%20be%20known%2C%20to%20attain%20identity%2C%20is%20to%20have%20a%20name.%20The%20nameless%2C%20wandering%20in%20search%20of%20the%20wholeness%20of%20black%20(%E2%80%9Cblack-wholic%E2%80%9D)%2C%20having%20been%20denied%20a%20name%2C%20in%20the%20trance%20of%20metaphors%2C%20becoming%20homeless%2C%20nomadic%20%E2%80%A6%20finally%20%E2%80%9Cretreat%20into%20self%20annihilation%20beyond%20verse%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20in%20these%20uncertainties%20that%20forms%20of%20knowledge%20like%20science%2C%20philosophy%2C%20and%20history%20enter%20a%2Fnil%E2%80%99s%20poetry.%20In%20the%20light%20of%20such%20epistemes%2C%20his%20poetry%20shines%20brightly.%20However%2C%20nothing%20is%20taken%20for%20granted%20or%20accepted%20as%20a%20given.%20All%20these%20appearances%20are%20corrected%20and%20reconstructed%20under%20the%20pressure%20of%20the%20Dalit%20experience.%20History%20is%20corrected%20to%20herstory.%20Philosophy%20becomes%20%3Cem%3Ephilosuffering%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Fetters%20accompany%20profit.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20mad%20demise%20of%20dirty%20boy%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cem%3ERetains%20its%20clarity%2C%20the%20glass%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cem%3EMirroring%20the%20mirror%20which%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cem%3EMirrors%20the%20clarity%20of%20history%20(Unplannable%20Supplement)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98History%20is%20a%20nightmare%20from%20which%20I%20am%20trying%20to%20awaken.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cem%3EHerstory%2C%20the%20correcting%20fluid%2C%20the%20white%20solution%20against%20the%20nightmarish.%20(%E2%80%9CPre%20face%E2%80%9D)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3Ethe%20philosuffer%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20profetter%20(Eithor)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20title%20%3Cem%3EEithor%3C%2Fem%3E%20tells%20us%20of%20the%20poet%E2%80%99s%20interest%20in%20ether%2C%20an%20abandoned%20scientific%20concept%2C%20and%20in%20the%20British%20polymath%20Thomas%20Young%E2%80%99s%20double-slit%20experiments%20that%20were%20instrumental%20in%20establishing%20the%20particle-wave%20duality%20of%20light.%20This%20made%20uncertain%20(either%2For)%20the%20precise%20nature%20of%20that%20which%20passed%20through%20the%20hole.%20Contemporary%20reality%20draws%20these%20words%20out%20of%20a%2Fnil%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20earth%20is%20supremely%20indifferent%20to%20the%20human%20race%20that%20breathes%20burden%20into%20earth%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cem%3EWith%20insubstantial%20plastics%20which%20will%20not%20leave%20her%20till%20she%20dies%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cem%3ELet%20the%20plastic%20eat%20us%2C%20sculpting%20our%20flesh%20and%20blood%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cem%3EWe%20shall%20all%20be%20plastic%20and%20insubstantial%3B%20we%20will%20melt%20in%20the%20fire%20and%20be%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20language%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%2Fnil%20writes%20lines%20reminiscent%20of%20Paul%20Celan.%20The%20latter%20once%20visited%20the%20German%20philosopher%20Martin%20Heidegger%2C%20given%20their%20shared%20interest%20in%20language%20and%20poetry.%20A%2Fnil%E2%80%99s%20staging%20of%20this%20meeting%20forces%20us%20to%20think%20about%20the%20contradictions%20in%20their%20lives.%20Heidegger%20was%20a%20member%20of%20Hitler%E2%80%99s%20Nazi%20party%2C%20and%20Celan%20was%20a%20Jew%20who%20worked%20in%20Nazi%20labour%20camps%20and%20escaped%20murder%20(his%20father%20died%20of%20disease%20and%20his%20mother%20was%20shot%20by%20soldiers%20in%20a%20concentration%20camp).%20They%20were%20interested%20in%20each%20other%E2%80%99s%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESome%20see%20their%20meeting%20as%20a%20milestone%20in%2020th-century%20intellectual%20history.%20(James%20K.%20Lyon%2C%20the%20author%20of%20%3Cem%3EPaul%20Celan%20and%20Martin%20Heidegger%3A%20An%20Unresolved%20Conversation%2C%201951%E2%80%931970%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20opens%20his%20book%20suggesting%20as%20much.)%20The%20poet%20must%20have%20expected%20a%20word%20of%20apology%20or%20remorse%20from%20the%20philosopher%20about%20the%20Nazi%20era%20and%20his%20involvement%20in%20it.%20As%20an%20epigraph%20to%20the%20poem%2C%20a%2Fnil%20quotes%20Celan%3A%20%E2%80%9COnly%20one%20thing%20remained%20reachable%2C%20close%20and%20secure%20amid%20all%20losses%3A%20language.%20Yes%2C%20language.%20In%20spite%20of%20everything%2C%20it%20remained%20secure%20against%20loss.%E2%80%9D%20During%20the%20meeting%2C%20the%20philosopher%20who%20had%20much%20to%20say%20about%20language%20remained%20silent%20about%20the%20holocaust.%20A%2Fnil%E2%80%99s%20poem%20evokes%20the%20weight%20of%20Celan%E2%80%99s%20dismay%20after%20that%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIn%20search%20of%20a%20dialogue%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cem%3EI%20talked%20to%20you%20over%20and%20over%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cem%3EIn%20desperation%2C%20in%20delirious%20fever%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cem%3EYou%20gave%20me%20no%20answers%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cem%3EYou%20were%20a%20shadow%20outside%20language%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cem%3EHomeless%20within%20language%2C%20nothing%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20poet%20sees%20a%20recurring%20paradox%20in%20Heidegger%E2%80%99s%20intellectual%20life.%20Years%20ago%2C%20I%20read%20an%20article%20by%20a%2Fnil%20in%20his%20now-defunct%20blog%20that%20every%20nature%20lover%20is%20a%20potential%20Nazi.%20He%20argued%20that%20dreams%20of%20a%20pristine%20natural%20society%20opposed%20to%20the%20brutal%20rule%20of%20capitalism%20were%20fundamental%20to%20fascist%20ideology.%20This%20may%20very%20well%20apply%20to%20Heidegger.%20Referring%20to%20Kasparov%E2%80%99s%20book%20%3Cem%3ELife%20Imitates%20Chess%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%2Fnil%20wrote%20that%20to%20counter%20the%20enemy%20one%20must%20apply%20their%20own%20methods%20and%20technologies%20of%20aggression%20against%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20same%20blog%20post%2C%20he%20wrote%20that%20the%20left-wing%20in%20India%20does%20not%20have%20any%20radical%20progressive%20programmes%3A%20%E2%80%9CAs%20Hegel%20has%20taught%20us%3A%20the%20radical%20conservative%20and%20the%20radical%20revolutionary%20have%20something%20in%20common.%20The%20tragedy%20is%20that%20in%20India%20we%20neither%20have%20a%20radical%20believer%20nor%20a%20radical%20revolutionary.%20We%20have%20only%20the%20liberal%20left%20and%20the%20liberal%20right.%20And%20they%20are%20the%20same%20lot.%20Like%20a%20bourgeoisie%20broker%20in%20the%20stock%20market%2C%20both%20Prakash%20Karat%20%5Bof%20the%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Marxist)%5D%20and%20Mar%20Andrews%20Thazhath%20%5Bthe%20archbishop%20of%20Thrissur%20in%20the%20Syro-Malabar%20Catholic%20Church%5D%20engage%20in%20profitable%20calculations%20in%20the%20globalised%20market!%E2%80%9D%20In%20another%20blog%20post%2C%20Anil%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9C%20%E2%80%A6%20it%20is%20impossible%20to%20criticise%20the%20Indian%20left%20because%20every%20radical%20questioning%20had%20already%20been%20incorporated%20into%20the%20leftist%20frame.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAll%20utopias%2C%20old%20and%20new%2C%20have%20now%20grown%20distant.%20Money%20has%20become%20God.%20But%20what%20of%20the%20desires%20whose%20value%20cannot%20be%20measured%3F%20The%20poet%20considers%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20determination%20to%20embrace%20Buddhism%20using%20the%20metaphor%20of%20August%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweb.mit.edu%2Fredingtn%2Fwww%2Fnetadv%2FSP20151130.html%5C%22%3EKekul%C3%A9%E2%80%99s%20dream%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20was%20a%20dream%20that%20inspired%20the%20scientist%20Kekul%C3%A9%20to%20discover%20the%20ring-like%20structure%20of%20benzene%3A%20a%20snake%20biting%20its%20own%20tail.%20There%20are%20interpreters%20of%20dreams%20who%20maintain%20that%20Kekul%C3%A9%E2%80%99s%20dream%20indicates%20fidelity%20in%20relationships.%20There%20are%20those%20who%20believe%20that%20dreamers%20open%20themselves%20up%20and%20are%20inspired%20by%20new%20experiences%20and%20ideas.%20It%20is%20an%20unconscious%20vision%20of%20renewal%2C%20transformation%2C%20a%20new%20life.%20In%20dreams%20one%20can%20unlock%20potentialities%2C%20and%20conceptualise%20destinations.%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20conversion%20to%20Buddhism%20possessed%20a%20unique%20dream%20and%20hope.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Buddha%20and%20his%20dhamma%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cem%3EAnd%20Ambedkar%20is%20well%20in%20Kekul%C3%A9%E2%80%99s%20dream%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20we%20read%20these%20poems%2C%20we%20encounter%20an%20author%20seeking%20acquaintance%20with%20Ambedkar%20and%20hoping%20to%20bear%20the%20burden%20of%20his%20ideas%20himself.%20Not%20only%20are%20Ambedkar%20and%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20politics%20the%20soul%20of%20these%20poems%2C%20a%2Fnil%20goes%20one%20step%20further%20and%20writes%20with%20an%20intense%20conviction%20about%20his%20own%20politics.%20Elsewhere%2C%20he%20has%20expressed%20his%20affinity%20for%20%C5%BDi%C5%BEek.%20%E2%80%9C%20%E2%80%A6%20he%20%5B%C5%BDi%C5%BEek%5D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fblogs%2FMain-Street%2Fwas-gandhi-more-violent-than%2F%5C%22%3Emaintains%20that%20Ambedkar%20was%20far%20more%20radical%20than%20Gandhi%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20that%20Gandhi%20was%20more%20violent%20than%20Hitler%3B%20he%20says%20one%20can%20learn%20more%20about%20India%20not%20from%20its%20monuments%20that%20are%20displayed%20for%20the%20tourist%E2%80%99s%20gaze%20but%20from%20the%20Dalits%20who%20clean%20the%20shit%20that%20tourists%20deposit%20in%20the%20toilet.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESeveral%20words%20recur%20in%20a%2Fnil%E2%80%99s%20poems.%20I%20will%20highlight%20three%20of%20them%3A%20crystal%2C%20menstruation%2C%20and%20sacrifice.%20Why%20is%20the%20poet%20drawn%20to%20these%20words%3F%20Why%20are%20they%20important%3F%20%E2%80%9CTransparency%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20perhaps%20the%20poet%20believes%20that%20being%20clear%20as%20crystal%20ought%20to%20be%20the%20bedrock%20of%20democracy%20and%20of%20all%20relationships.%20%E2%80%9CMenstruation%E2%80%9D%20could%20signify%20the%20changes%20of%20the%20seasons%2C%20carries%20the%20hope%20of%20an%20approaching%20spring.%20A%2Fnil%20also%20wants%20this%20word%20to%20invoke%20the%20opposite%20sense%20of%20melancholy%20and%20despair.%20The%20word%20%E2%80%9Csacrifice%E2%80%9D%20appears%20in%20these%20poems%20as%20the%20consciousness%20that%20abandons%20idealism%20and%20absolute%20values%20for%20the%20welfare%20of%20the%20world.%20The%20exchange%20sacrifice%20in%20chess%2C%20which%20the%20poet%20portrays%20as%20the%20most%20desirable%20form%20of%20sacrifice%2C%20upturns%20the%20commonsensical%20connotations%20surrounding%20the%20signifier.%20A%2Fnil%E2%80%99s%20poetry%20sets%20in%20motion%20a%20great%20process%2C%20whereby%20words%20are%20constantly%20renewed%20and%20led%20to%20new%20meanings%20and%20values.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20life%20of%20words%20in%20these%20poems%20is%20not%20satisfied%20or%20fulfilled%20in%20poetry%20alone.%20They%20open%20themselves%20up%20to%20philosophy%2C%20science%2C%20the%20arts%2C%20and%20other%20human%20discourses.%20Deleuze%E2%80%99s%20visions%20that%20science%2C%20philosophy%2C%20and%20literature%20can%20share%20spaces%20and%20spill%20into%20each%20other%20are%20realised%20in%20a%2Fnil%E2%80%99s%20poetry.%20It%20has%20a%20density%20of%20meaning%20and%20instruction%20that%20makes%20the%20reader%20want%20to%20immerse%20themselves%20in%20the%20worlds%20that%20a%2Fnil%E2%80%99s%20words%20conjure.%20Readers%20will%20realise%20that%20as%20they%20read%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Absent%20Color%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%2Fnil%20disappears.%20He%20is%20no%20longer%20the%20poet%20or%20the%20critic%20or%20the%20interpreter%20or%20even%20the%20writer.%20The%20words%20speak%20for%20themselves%20and%20the%20poem%20declares%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EV.%20Vijayakumar%20is%20a%20retired%20associate%20professor%20of%20Physics%20at%20Government%20Victoria%20College%2C%20Palakkad%2C%20Kerala.%20He%20writes%20on%20literature%2C%20cinema%2C%20culture%2C%20and%20science.%20His%20notable%20works%20include%3C%2Fem%3E%20Shastravum%20Tatvachintayum%20(Science%20and%20Philosophy)%2C%20Quantum%20Bhautikattile%20Darshanika%20Prashnangal%20(The%20Philosophical%20Issues%20in%20Quantum%20Physics)%2C%20Uttaradhunika%20Shastram%20(The%20Postmodern%20Science)%2C%20and%20Kathayillattatu%20(The%20Nonsensical).%20%3Cem%3EHe%20is%20a%20recipient%20of%20the%20G.N.%20Pillai%20Award%20(2020)%20from%20the%20Kerala%20Sahitya%20Academy%2C%20the%20N.V.%20Krishna%20Warrier%20Memorial%20Award%20(2007)%20from%20the%20Kerala%20Bhasha%20Institute%2C%20and%20the%20Best%20Film%20Critic%20Award%20(2013)%20from%20the%20Government%20of%20Kerala.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Absent%20Color%20%3Cem%3Ewas%20launched%20in%20New%20Delhi%20at%20the%20India%20International%20Centre%20(Annexe)%2C%20on%20November%205%2C%202023.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699266706000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F06152247%2Fimage-1479.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-absent-color-mapping-the-contours-of-a-nil-world-a-trial-for-imagination%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22When%20the%20poet%20writes%20his%20name%20in%20English%20as%20%E2%80%9Ca%2Fnil%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20abandons%20all%20valour%2C%20heroism%2C%20and%20hierarchical%20symbols%20of%20power%20embodied%20in%20language%20and%20appears%20before%20us%20as%20a%2Fnil%2C%20a%2Fvoid%2C%20in%20the%20lowercase%2C%20bare%2C%20unassertive%2C%20claiming%20nothing.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-absent-color-mapping-the-contours-of-a-nil-world-a-trial-for-imagination%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Cliff%20face%20shop%20dubbed%20'inconvenient%20convenience%20store'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699265880000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F11%2F768x432%2Fskynews-shiniuzhai-cliff-convenience-store_6350346.jpg%3F20231106105106%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fcliff-face-shop-in-chinas-hunan-province-dubbed-inconvenient-convenience-store-13001868%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20tiny%20shop%20hanging%20from%20the%20side%20of%20a%20steep%20cliff%20face%20has%20been%20nicknamed%20the%20most%20%26quot%3Binconvenient%20convenience%20store%26quot%3B%20in%20China%20for%20supplying%20refreshments%20to%20climbers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A521%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fcliff-face-shop-in-chinas-hunan-province-dubbed-inconvenient-convenience-store-13001868%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fcliff-face-shop-in-chinas-hunan-province-dubbed-inconvenient-convenience-store-13001868%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fcliff-face-shop-in-chinas-hunan-province-dubbed-inconvenient-convenience-store-13001868%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mohan%20Bhagwat%20May%20Quote%20Ambedkar%2C%20But%20RSS%20Is%20Polar%20Opposite%20of%20His%20Ideology%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F14124741%2FIMG_1874-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ideologies%20of%20the%20RSS%20and%20B.R.%20Ambedkar%20can%20be%20called%20two%20opposite%20poles%20of%20the%20Indian%20political%20spectrum.%20While%20Ambedkar%20stood%20for%20the%20annihilation%20of%20caste%2C%20struggled%20for%20democratic%20values%20and%20marched%20towards%20social%20justice%2C%20the%20RSS%20stands%20for%20the%20status%20quo%20and%20the%20revival%20of%20the%20hierarchical%20value%20system%20of%20pre-modern%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20ironic%20that%20despite%20these%20core%20contradictions%2C%20RSS%20ideologues%20try%20to%20make%20a%20show%20of%20paying%20respect%20to%20Ambedkar%20in%20various%20forums%2C%20including%20celebrating%20his%20birth%20anniversary.%20So%20in%20a%20way%2C%20it%20was%20not%20surprising%20when%20RSS%20chief%20Mohan%20Bhagwat%20in%20his%20annual%20Vijyadashami%20speech%20on%20October%2024%20called%20upon%20his%20followers%20to%20read%20speeches%20of%20Ambedkar%2C%20particularly%20the%20last%20two%20speeches%20delivered%20by%20him%20in%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly.%20Bhagawat%20went%20to%20the%20extent%20of%20putting%20Ambedkar%20in%20the%20same%20category%20as%20RSS%20founder%20and%20first%20%3Cem%3Esarsanghchalak%3C%2Fem%3E%20(chief)%20K.B.%20Hedgewar.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUsually%2C%20the%20response%20of%20RSS%20types%20to%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20quest%20for%20equality%20has%20been%20to%20oppose%20his%20efforts%20at%20an%20ideological%20level%20under%20the%20garb%20of%20%E2%80%98our%20glorious%20past%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20such%2C%20the%20struggle%20for%20social%20justice%20which%20initially%20came%20up%20in%20the%20form%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98Non-Brahmin%20Movement%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20Nagpur%20area%20of%20Vidarbha%20was%20one%20of%20the%20major%20reasons%20for%20the%20landlord-Brahmin%20alliance%20of%20this%20region%20to%20form%20RSS.%20In%20Maharashtra%2C%20this%20alliance%20is%20called%20Shetji-Bhatji.%20The%20Dalit%20awakening%20began%20with%20Jyotirao%20Phule%20who%20struggled%20to%20open%20schools%20for%20oppressed%20castes.%20It%20was%20backed%20up%20and%20enhanced%20by%20Ambedkar%20starting%20the%20newspaper%20%3Ci%3EMooknayak%3C%2Fi%3E%20in%201920%20and%20the%20Bahujan%20Hitkarini%20Sabha%20in%201923.%20These%20might%20have%20added%20tremendously%20to%20the%20awakening.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELater%20in%20his%20pursuit%20of%20social%20justice%20Ambedkar%20organised%20the%20Chavdar%20Tale%20Satyagraha%20(access%20to%20public%20drinking%20water%20for%20Dalits)%20in%201927%20and%20the%20Kalaram%20Temple%20entry%20movement%20in%201930.%20The%20RSS%20itself%20is%20never%20known%20to%20have%20come%20forward%20to%20support%20these%20movements%20of%20Babasaheb.%20Among%20upper%20caste%20leaders%2C%20it%20was%20only%20Gandhi%20who%20took%20up%20the%20issue%20of%20caste%20most%20seriously%20and%20devoted%20time%20to%20improving%20the%20plight%20of%20Dalits%20in%20the%20years%20after%20the%20Poona%20Pact%20of%201932.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20RSS%20was%20propagating%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20Hindu%20rashtra.%20V.D.%20Savarkar%20was%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20the%20theory%20of%20the%20two-nation%20theory%2C%20the%20Hindu%20Nation%20and%20the%20Muslim%20Nation.%20This%20Hindu%20nation%20theory%20propagated%20by%20the%20RSS%20came%20under%20severe%20criticism%20from%20Ambedkar%20as%20he%20wrote%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CStrange%20as%20it%20may%20appear%2C%20Mr.%20Savarkar%20and%20Mr.%20Jinnah%2C%20instead%20of%20being%20opposed%20to%20each%20other%20on%20the%20one%20nation%20versus%20two%20nations%20issue%2C%20are%20in%20complete%20agreement%20about%20it.%20Both%20agree%20not%20only%20agree%2C%20but%20insist%20that%20there%20are%20two%20nations%20in%20India%E2%80%94one%20the%20Muslim%20nation%20and%20the%20other%20the%20Hindu%20nation.%E2%80%9D%20%5B%3C%2Fem%3EThoughts%20on%20Pakistan%3Cem%3E%20(1940)%5D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmbedkar%20was%20totally%20opposed%20to%20the%20concept%20of%20a%20Hindu%20Nation.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20Hindu%20Raj%20does%20become%20a%20fact%2C%20it%20will%2C%20no%20doubt%2C%20be%20the%20greatest%20calamity%20for%20this%20country.%E2%80%A6%20Hindu%20Raj%20must%20be%20prevented%20at%20any%20cost%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20wrote%20in%20%3Ci%3EPakistan%20or%20the%20Partition%20of%20India%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0(1946%2C%20pages%20354-355).%20He%20was%20against%20majoritarianism%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffrontline.thehindu.com%2Fcover-story%2Fambedkars-warning%2Farticle23595905.ece%5C%22%3Ewhich%20in%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Indian%20context%20meant%20the%20unbridled%20rule%20of%20the%20majority%20community%2C%20the%20Hindus.%20This%20is%20the%20current%20dominant%20ideology%20of%20the%20RSS%20led%20by%20Bhagwat%20as%20Narendra%20Modi%20has%20come%20forward%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Fopinion%2Fpm-modi-asked-what-is-wrong-with-majoritarianism-its-a-fair-question%2F1811497%2F%5C%22%3Edefend%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20by%20asking%20what%20is%20wrong%20with%20majoritarianism.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20presentation%20of%20the%20final%20draft%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20the%20RSS%E2%80%99s%20opposition%20came%20its%20mouthpiece%2C%20%3Cem%3EOrganiser%3C%2Fem%3E.%20A%20scathing%20editorial%20in%20the%20November%201949%20edition%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fram_guha%2Fstatus%2F1250751644293193728%3Flang%3Dzh-Hant%5C%22%3Eread%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20worst%20%5Bthing%5D%20about%20the%20new%20Constitution%20of%20Bharat%E2%80%A6is%20that%20there%20is%20nothing%20Bharatiya%20about%20it%E2%80%A6%20%5BT%5Dhere%20is%20no%20trace%20of%20ancient%20Bharatiya%20constitutional%20laws%2C%20institutions%2C%20nomenclature%20and%20phraseology%20in%20it%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Hindu%20Code%20Bill%20drafted%20by%20Ambedkar%20was%20a%20major%20step%20in%20efforts%20towards%20loosening%20the%20hold%20of%20patriarchy%20and%20striving%20for%20equality%20for%20women.%20The%20orthodox%20forces%20led%20by%20the%20RSS%20frontally%20attacked%20it.%20Ramachandra%20Guha%2C%20the%20eminent%20historian%20of%20modern%20India%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fbhagwat-ambedkar-rss-8997717%2F%5C%22%3Ewrites%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Sangh%20opposed%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20Hindu%20Code%20Bill%20that%20sought%20to%20give%20Hindu%20women%20the%20right%20to%20marry%20outside%20their%20caste%2C%20divorce%20their%20husband%2C%20and%20inherit%20property.%20In%201949%2C%20the%20RSS%20organized%20hundreds%20of%20meetings%20and%20protests%20across%20India%20to%20stop%20the%20bill%2C%20where%20sadhus%20and%20sants%20came%20to%20speak.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Constituent%20Assembly%20in%20its%20wisdom%20enunciated%20the%20provisions%20of%20reservation%20for%20Scheduled%20Castes%20and%20and%20Scheduled%20Tribes.%20Through%20word-of-mouth%20propaganda%2C%20these%20provisions%20were%20undermined%20and%20defamed%20by%20right-wing%20leaders%2C%20which%20led%20to%20anti-Dalit%20violence%20in%20Gujarat%20in%201980-1981%20and%20again%20in%201985.%20Similarly%2C%20reservations%20for%20the%20OBCs%2C%20under%20the%20Mandal%20Commission%2C%20were%20indirectly%20opposed%20when%20%3Cem%3Erath%20yatras%3C%2Fem%3E%20for%20a%20Ram%20temple%20in%20Ayodhya%20were%20jacked%20up%20and%20then%20BJP%20leader%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%20stated%20something%20to%20the%20effect%20of%20%E2%80%9CThey%20brought%20Mandal%2C%20so%20we%20brought%20Kamadal.%E2%80%9D%20Interestingly%2C%20the%20Sangh%20%3Cem%3Eparivar%3C%2Fem%3E%20oversaw%20the%20demolition%20of%20the%20Babri%20masjid%20on%20December%206%2C%20the%20death%20anniversary%20of%20Ambedkar%2C%20a%20tactical%20move%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fhow-bjp-overshadows-dates-related-to-ambedkar-and-the-constitution%5C%22%3Eundermine%20the%20importance%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20this%20day%20for%20democratic%20values.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20far%20as%20the%20status%20of%20religious%20minorities%20was%20concerned%2C%20Ambedkar%20wanted%20to%20grant%20full%20protective%20clauses.%20Though%20these%20clauses%20have%20not%20been%20implemented%20in%20full%20at%20any%20time%20in%20Independent%20India%E2%80%99s%20history%2C%20the%20attempt%20to%20implement%20them%20is%20labelled%20as%20%E2%80%98minority%20appeasement%E2%80%99.%20Babasaheb%20was%20for%20implementing%20the%20concept%20of%20Fraternity%3B%20on%20the%20contrary%2C%20the%20politics%20of%20majoritarianism%20has%20spread%20hatred%20against%20minorities%2C%20leading%20to%20violence%20and%20polarisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20concept%20of%20social%20democracy%20was%20an%20inalienable%20part%20of%20democracy%20as%20far%20as%20Ambedkar%20was%20concerned.%20He%20was%20for%20the%20annihilation%20of%20caste.%20RSS%2C%20on%20the%20contrary%2C%20has%20founded%20%E2%80%9CSamajik%20Samrasta%20Manch%E2%80%9D%20(Social%20Harmony%20Forum).%20For%20RSS%2C%20different%20castes%20were%20part%20of%20the%20whole%2C%20giving%20strength%20to%20Hindu%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHere%20lies%20the%20major%20opposition%20between%20the%20ideology%20of%20these%20two%20streams.%20Hindu%20majoritarian%20politics%20attempts%20to%20maintain%20the%20caste%20hierarchy%20in%20newer%20terminologies.%20While%20paying%20lip%20service%20to%20the%20Indian%20constitution%2C%20ideologues%20of%20Hindu%20majoritarianism%20argue%20that%20India%20is%20a%20%E2%80%98civilisational%20state%E2%80%99%20(symbol%20for%20caste%20and%20gender%20hierarchical%20values%20in%20scriptures%20like%20Manusmriti)%20where%20the%20constitution%20should%20be%20secondary!%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECleverly%2C%20while%20being%20opposed%20to%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20ideology%2C%20the%20Sangh%20parivar%20is%20paying%20lip%20service%20to%20him%20and%20now%20even%20quoting%20him.%20This%20is%20a%20clever%20ploy%20meant%20purely%20for%20electoral%20purposes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fram-puniyani%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERam%20Puniyani%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20president%20of%20the%20Centre%20of%20Study%20of%20Society%20and%20Secularism.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699264846000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F14124741%2FIMG_1874-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fmohan-bhagwat-ambedkar-rss-polar-opposite-ideology%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20is%20ironic%20that%20despite%20core%20contradictions%20in%20ideologies%2C%20RSS%20leaders%20make%20a%20show%20of%20paying%20respect%20to%20Ambedkar%20for%20electoral%20gains.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A30%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fmohan-bhagwat-ambedkar-rss-polar-opposite-ideology%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Driving%20restrictions%20to%20come%20into%20force%20in%20one%20of%20world's%20most%20polluted%20cities%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699262700000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F11%2F768x432%2Fskynews-delhi-india-cars-pollution_6350426.jpg%3F20231106114149%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fnew-delhi-driving-restrictions-to-come-into-force-as-air-pollution-levels-remain-severe-13001840%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India's%20capital%20is%20bringing%20in%20odd-even%20vehicle%20number%20plate%20restrictions%20to%20curb%20air%20pollution.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A154%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fnew-delhi-driving-restrictions-to-come-into-force-as-air-pollution-levels-remain-severe-13001840%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fnew-delhi-driving-restrictions-to-come-into-force-as-air-pollution-levels-remain-severe-13001840%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fnew-delhi-driving-restrictions-to-come-into-force-as-air-pollution-levels-remain-severe-13001840%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22NITI%20Aayog%20Considers%20Discontinuing%20Key%20Report%20on%20Water%20Management%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F19165415%2Fimage-1409.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Government%20policy%20think-tank%20NITI%20Aayog%20is%20said%20to%20have%20marked%20reports%20on%20water%20management%20in%20states%20for%20the%20years%202018-19%20and%202019-20%20for%20%E2%80%9Cinternal%20use%E2%80%9D%20after%20releasing%20previous%20editions%20publicly%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fniti-weighs-discontinuing-key-water-report-launched-5-years-ago-9015084%2F%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20%E2%80%98Composite%20Water%20Management%20Index%E2%80%99%20(CWMI)%2C%20first%20published%20in%20June%202018%2C%20ranked%20states%20in%20terms%20of%20efficacy%20of%20water%20management%20on%20the%20basis%20of%2028%20parameters.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20edition%20provided%20data%20for%202015-16%20and%202016-17%2C%20and%20the%20second%20edition%20launched%20in%20August%202019%20was%20for%202017-18.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%2C%20published%20by%20NITI%20Aayog%2C%20was%20prepared%20in%20association%20with%20three%20ministries%20%E2%80%93%20Water%20Resources%2C%20Drinking%20Water%20%26amp%3B%20Sanitation%2C%20and%20Rural%20Development.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report%2C%20the%20apex%20government%20policy%20think%20tank%20wrote%20to%20the%20Union%20Ministry%20of%20Jal%20Shakti%2C%20seeking%20their%20perspective%20on%20the%20%E2%80%9Cuse%20and%20applicability%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20report%20and%20whether%20the%20CWMI%20should%20continue.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fniti-weighs-discontinuing-key-water-report-launched-5-years-ago-9015084%2F%5C%22%3ENo%20response%20was%20received%20from%20the%20ministry%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20the%20third%20and%20fourth%20editions%20await%20release%2C%20the%20paper%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20NITI%20Aayog%20spokesperson%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fniti-weighs-discontinuing-key-water-report-launched-5-years-ago-9015084%2F%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%3Cem%3E%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20the%20reports%20may%20be%20clubbed%20with%20those%20for%20the%20next%20two%20years%20(2020%20and%202021).%20There%20have%20also%20been%20talks%20of%20other%20channels%20being%20explored%20for%20the%20task%20of%20indexing%20instead%20of%20sole%20reliance%20on%20the%20CWMI%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20discussed%20in%20a%20meeting%20between%20NITI%20Aayog%20member%20Ramesh%20Chand%20and%20officers%20of%20the%20Jal%20Shakti%20Ministry%20on%20December%2012%2C%202022.%20Nearly%20five%20months%20after%20this%20meeting%2C%20the%20NITI%20Aayog%20sent%20letters%20to%20Department%20of%20Water%20Resources%2C%20River%20Development%20and%20Ganga%20Rejuvenation%20and%20the%20Department%20of%20Drinking%20Water%20and%20Sanitation%2C%20both%20of%20which%20come%20under%20the%20Jal%20Shakti%20Ministry%2C%20saying%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20Member%20(economist%20Ramesh%20Chand)%20is%20of%20the%20view%20that%20other%20channels%20need%20to%20be%20explored%20to%20undertake%20the%20task%20of%20indexing%20rather%20than%20relying%20only%20on%20CWMI%20and%20that%20the%20CWMI%20is%20not%20widely%20used%20or%20applied%20in%20Planning%2C%20Decision%20making%2C%20Policy%20Formulation%20or%20Research%20by%20public%20or%20private%20stakeholders%20concerned%20with%20water%20sector%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20Indian%20Express%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20report%2C%20a%20copy%20of%20which%20has%20been%20seen%20by%20paper%2C%20points%20out%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fniti-weighs-discontinuing-key-water-report-launched-5-years-ago-9015084%2F%5C%22%3Ewater%20scarcity%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Cnational%20problem%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E.%20According%20to%20the%20Jal%20Shakti%20Ministry%2C%20the%20average%20annual%20per%20capita%20water%20availability%20is%20projected%20to%20decline%20to%201%2C486%20cubic%20meters%20per%20person%20per%20year%20by%202021%20as%20compared%20to%201%2C545%20cubic%20meters%20per%20person%20per%20year%20in%202011.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20accordance%20with%20the%20annual%20water%20availability%20norms%2C%20a%20value%20below%201%2C700%20cubic%20meter%2Fperson%2Fyear%20indicates%20water%20shortage%20while%20that%20below%201%2C000%20cubic%20metre%2Fcapita%2Fyear%20is%20considered%20as%20%E2%80%9Cscarcity%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20has%20been%20under%20the%20scanner%20for%20suppressing%20data%20that%20may%20prove%20electorally%20unfavourable.%20In%20the%20past%20the%20Modi%20government%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fnarendra-modi-data-npr-nrc-economy%5C%22%3Edelayed%20the%20release%20of%20data%20or%20claimed%20that%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20have%20any%20numbers%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20key%20factors%20like%20unemployment%2C%20poverty%2C%20consumer%20spending%2C%20mob%20lynching%2C%20farmer%20suicides%2C%20GDP%20growth%20and%20the%20caste%20census%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699262110000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F19165415%2Fimage-1409.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fniti-aayog-considers-discontinuing-key-report-on-water-management%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20latest%20report%20points%20out%20that%20water%20scarcity%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Cnational%20problem%E2%80%9D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fniti-aayog-considers-discontinuing-key-report-on-water-management%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3